content:
Certainly! Below is an example of a JSON data format that stores information about some of the largest cities in the world by population. Each city entry includes the city name, country, population, the year the population was last recorded, and a nested array with the coordinates of the city's location (latitude and longitude).

```json
{
  "cities": [
    {
      "name": "Tokyo",
      "country": "Japan",
      "population": 37435191,
      "year_recorded": 2023,
      "coordinates": {
        "latitude": 35.6895,
        "longitude": 139.6917
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Delhi",
      "country": "India",
      "population": 30290936,
      "year_recorded": 2023,
      "coordinates": {
        "latitude": 28.6139,
        "longitude": 77.2090
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Shanghai",
      "country": "China",
      "population": 27058479,
      "year_recorded": 2023,
      "coordinates": {
        "latitude": 31.2304,
        "longitude": 121.4737
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "São Paulo",
      "country": "Brazil",
      "population": 22043028,
      "year_recorded": 2023,
      "coordinates": {
        "latitude": -23.5505,
        "longitude": -46.6333
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Mexico City",
      "country": "Mexico",
      "population": 21918936,
      "year_recorded": 2023,
      "coordinates": {
        "latitude": 19.4326,
        "longitude": -99.1332
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

This JSON structure should allow you to easily access and manipulate information about these cities, including their geographic coordinates.
